Throughout the semester, mentors meet up regularly with their mentees, giving advice, sharing their experience and helping the mentee through any hardships they might have.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to provide senior students of computer science, mathematics and mathematical statistics with the skills and knowledge in order to turn them into mentors for freshmen. The mentors introduce the developmental opportunities that the university has to offer and help out with the social side of university life.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Passer of the subject: -has acquired social leadership skills by directing freshmen students to appropriate activities / events -is able to arrange / offer suitable activities to freshmen students -is able to share university experience -knows the main concerns / problems of studying at the university -is able to give appropriate advice in resolving these problems
